00:25:31.130 --> 00:25:33.440
What's fishy about it?

00:25:33.440 --> 00:25:35.966
Why the sudden love
for the radius?

00:25:35.966 --> 00:25:37.840
I thought circles were
about their diameters.

00:25:37.840 --> 00:25:40.370
We're dividing out
by D. So we really

00:25:40.370 --> 00:25:42.680
should write this, in
order to be consistent,

00:25:42.680 --> 00:25:45.811
as A equals one quarter pi D
squared, which isn't nearly as

00:25:45.811 --> 00:25:46.310
pretty.

00:25:48.292 --> 00:25:50.750
All right, so let's figure out
what's really going on here.

00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:53.360
Let's look at this expression.

00:25:53.360 --> 00:25:57.290
I want to draw your attention
here to the power of 2.

00:25:57.290 --> 00:25:59.510
That second power makes
this a particularly simple

00:25:59.510 --> 00:26:01.410
quadratic form.

00:26:01.410 --> 00:26:04.280
The name mathematicians use
for this kind of expression.

00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:07.070
Now I want to show
you some examples

00:26:07.070 --> 00:26:09.350
of the kind of patterns
that quadratic forms follow.

00:26:09.350 --> 00:26:11.120
And for this, I'm going
to draw on my background

00:26:11.120 --> 00:26:12.078
of theoretical physics.

00:26:12.078 --> 00:26:13.220
I have a PhD from Cal Tech.

00:26:13.220 --> 00:26:14.900
And when I was a
graduate student,

00:26:14.900 --> 00:26:17.596
I taught the physics core
curriculum for five years.

00:26:17.596 --> 00:26:19.970
And I'd like to show you some
examples of quadratic forms

00:26:19.970 --> 00:26:22.010
that arise in the elementary
physics curriculum.

00:26:22.010 --> 00:26:24.260
It's not necessary to
understand all the details here.

00:26:24.260 --> 00:26:27.350
Just look for the
high level patterns.

00:26:27.350 --> 00:26:30.740
We're going to start with a
calculation for the distance

00:26:30.740 --> 00:26:33.270
an object falls in a
particular amount of time.

00:26:33.270 --> 00:26:37.820
So Galileo Galilei found
that the velocity of a

00:26:37.820 --> 00:26:40.290
dropped object is proportional
to the time it's fallen.

00:26:40.290 --> 00:26:44.730
So if it falls twice as
long, it goes twice as fast.

00:26:44.730 --> 00:26:46.350
The constant of
proportionality is

00:26:46.350 --> 00:26:49.950
the gravitational acceleration
G. In this context,

00:26:49.950 --> 00:26:52.200
the velocity can be defined
as the time rate of change

00:26:52.200 --> 00:26:54.230
of the height, dy dt.

00:26:54.230 --> 00:26:59.700
So we can find the distance
fallen by integrating V dt.

00:26:59.700 --> 00:27:02.500
Which is the integral of G
dt, with G as just a constant.

00:27:02.500 --> 00:27:03.300
We can pull it out.

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:05.400
The integral of t
with t squared over 2.

00:27:05.400 --> 00:27:07.370
So y is equal to 1/2 Gt squared.

00:27:09.974 --> 00:27:11.640
We can also look at
the potential energy

00:27:11.640 --> 00:27:13.950
in a spring, another
common thing that

00:27:13.950 --> 00:27:16.020
shows up in the elementary
physics curriculum.

00:27:16.020 --> 00:27:19.590
Robert Hooke showed that the
force that a spring exerts

00:27:19.590 --> 00:27:21.930
to restored equilibrium
is proportional

00:27:21.930 --> 00:27:24.270
to the displacement
from equilibrium.

00:27:24.270 --> 00:27:26.910
And the cause of
proportionality is essentially

00:27:26.910 --> 00:27:29.100
a measure of the
stiffness of the spring,

00:27:29.100 --> 00:27:32.490
is the spring constant k.

00:27:32.490 --> 00:27:34.740
And the potential energy
is equal to the work

00:27:34.740 --> 00:27:38.020
done by the spring force, as
you compress it or stretch it.

00:27:38.020 --> 00:27:40.360
U is equal to integral of Fdx.

00:27:40.360 --> 00:27:42.640
Integrate the force
over the distance.

00:27:42.640 --> 00:27:47.865
So you say U equals Fdx, and
Fdx equals integral from zero up

00:27:47.865 --> 00:27:50.640
to the final displacement
of kx dx, which

00:27:50.640 --> 00:27:52.200
is equal to 1/2 kx squared.

00:27:54.900 --> 00:27:56.960
And finally, I want to
show you the calculation

00:27:56.960 --> 00:27:59.459
for the kinetic energy, one of
the most important quantities

00:27:59.459 --> 00:28:01.010
in mechanics.

00:28:01.010 --> 00:28:03.170
Isaac Newton found
that the force

00:28:03.170 --> 00:28:06.800
is proportional to
the acceleration.

00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:09.780
The concept proportionality
is the inertial mass n.

00:28:09.780 --> 00:28:12.500
This is the most famous
expression of Newton's Second

00:28:12.500 --> 00:28:14.912
Law of Motion, f equals na.

00:28:14.912 --> 00:28:17.120
Now the kinetic energy is
equal to the amount of work

00:28:17.120 --> 00:28:21.290
done accelerating a mass m
up to a final velocity of e.

00:28:21.290 --> 00:28:23.671
So that's the integral of the
force over the displacement

00:28:23.671 --> 00:28:24.170
again.

00:28:24.170 --> 00:28:26.450
So k is equal to
interval of Fdx,

00:28:26.450 --> 00:28:29.720
but the force is mass
times acceleration.

00:28:29.720 --> 00:28:34.282
Acceleration is the time rate
of change of velocity, n Dvt.

00:28:34.282 --> 00:28:35.990
Now Newton would be
unhappy at this point

00:28:35.990 --> 00:28:39.070
because we are using the
notation of his hated rival,

00:28:39.070 --> 00:28:40.544
Gottfried Wilhelm von Leibniz.

00:28:40.544 --> 00:28:42.710
But one of the great things
about Leibniz's notation

00:28:42.710 --> 00:28:45.376
is that you can manipulate these
little differentials, these Ds,

00:28:45.376 --> 00:28:46.890
as if they were fractions.

00:28:46.890 --> 00:28:52.820
So we can write Dv
Dt Dx as m Dx Dt Dv.

00:28:52.820 --> 00:28:54.560
We can just swap
the Dx and the Dv.

00:28:54.560 --> 00:28:56.850
But this here is
just the velocity.

00:28:56.850 --> 00:28:58.610
So this is the
integral from zero up

00:28:58.610 --> 00:29:04.070
to the final velocity of
m Dv, or 1/2 m Dv squared.

00:29:04.070 --> 00:29:08.730
So just to review, distance
fallen, potential energy

00:29:08.730 --> 00:29:12.581
in the spring, kinetic energy.

00:29:12.581 --> 00:29:14.830
You may by now have a sense
of foreboding as we return

00:29:14.830 --> 00:29:18.170
to the geometry of the circle.

00:29:18.170 --> 00:29:21.070
Let's calculate the
area of a circular disk.

00:29:21.070 --> 00:29:25.390
We can do that by breaking
the disk into rings of length

00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:28.870
equal to the circumference of
that radius and thickness equal

00:29:28.870 --> 00:29:31.570
to Dr. So the area
is circumference

00:29:31.570 --> 00:29:35.910
times the thickness
of that ring.

00:29:35.910 --> 00:29:39.330
Now the circumference is
proportional to the radius.

00:29:39.330 --> 00:29:42.200
Constant proportionality is tau.

00:29:42.200 --> 00:29:44.220
You can calculate the
area of the circle

00:29:44.220 --> 00:29:46.500
by integrating
over all the rings.

00:29:46.500 --> 00:29:51.300
So a is equal to integral Da,
equals the integral of CDr,

00:29:51.300 --> 00:29:54.210
which is the integral from zero
up to the final radius of tau

00:29:54.210 --> 00:29:57.507
rDr, which is 1/2 tau r squared.

00:30:01.980 --> 00:30:05.400
Indeed, in the original proof
by Archimedes of Syracuse,

00:30:05.400 --> 00:30:07.679
he showed not that the
area was pi r squared.

00:30:07.679 --> 00:30:09.720
Archimedes didn't have
modern algebraic notation.

00:30:09.720 --> 00:30:12.630
What Archimedes proved was
that the area of a circle

00:30:12.630 --> 00:30:15.390
is the same as the area of
a right triangle with height

00:30:15.390 --> 00:30:19.020
equal to the radius, and base
equal to the circumference.

00:30:19.020 --> 00:30:21.660
We can then apply the formula
for the area of a triangle,

00:30:21.660 --> 00:30:24.180
area equals 1/2
base times height,

00:30:24.180 --> 00:30:31.190
as a equals 1/2 bh, equals 1/2
Cr, equals 1/2 tau r squared.

00:30:31.190 --> 00:30:33.380
There's simply no avoiding
that factor of a half.

